In their 2019 manifesto, the Conservatives promised to match the average EU subsidy of about £1.5billion a year to help deprived areas of the UK "at a minimum" after the Brexit referendum's pledge to "take back control" from the bloc. However, details of the Shared Prosperity fund show that over the next three years it will only hand out £2.6billion and will not match the EU funding level until 2025. Dan Jarvis, the South Yorkshire mayor, said: “This announcement is nothing more than an outrage; a cynical Conservative con that utterly fails South Yorkshire and drives a coach and horses through the Government’s levelling-up agenda. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES... 